1.2) Normalization

Let’s normalize the original dataset by randomly subsampling 686 reads in each station:

library(vegan)
TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_min686_t<-t(TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_min686)
TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_ss686<-rrarefy(TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_min686_t, 686)

length(which(colSums(TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_ss686)==0))

There are 1020 OTUs that don’t show any occurrence in the normalized data. Let’s remove them from the table and take a look at its final dimensions:

TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_ss686_no_cero<-TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_ss686[,-(which(colSums(TP_NR97_18S_miTags_tax_occur_ss686)==0))]
